obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (12062)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1 19th April, 2017 vide notification no. S.O. 1215 (E) dated 19th April, 2017 see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, Section 3 (ii).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12062&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Rights of Persons with`
  line `Disabilities Act, 2016.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (12063)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12063&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "appellate authority" means an authority notified under sub-section (3) of section 14 or`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 53 or designated under sub-section (1) of section 59, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) "appropriate Government" means,---`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to the Central Government or any establishment wholly or substantially`
  line `financed by that Government, or a Cantonment Board constituted under the Cantonments Act,`
  line `2006 (41 of 2006), the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a State Government or any establishment, wholly or substantially financed`
  line `by that Government, or any local authority, other than a Cantonment Board, the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(c) "barrier" means any factor including communicational, cultural, economic, environmental,`
  line `institutional, political, social, attitudinal or structural factors which hampers the full and effective`
  line `participation of persons with disabilities in society;`
  line
  line `(d) "care-giver" means any person including parents and other family Members who with or`
  line `without payment provides care, support or assistance to a person with disability;`
  line
  line `(e) "certifying authority" means an authority designated under sub-section (1) of section 57;`
  line
  line `(f) "communication" includes means and formats of communication, languages, display of text,`
  line `Braille, tactile communication, signs, large print, accessible multimedia, written, audio, video, visual`
  line `displays, sign language, plain-language, human-reader, augmentative and alternative modes and`
  line `accessible information and communication technology;`
  line
  line `(g) "competent authority" means an authority appointed under section 49;`
  line
  line `(h) "discrimination" in relation to disability, means any distinction, exclusion, restriction on the`
  line `basis of disability which is the purpose or effect of impairing or nullifying the recognition, enjoyment`
  line `or exercise on an equal basis with others of all human rights and fundamental freedoms in the`
  line `political, economic, social, cultural, civil or any other field and includes all forms of discrimination`
  line `and denial of reasonable accommodation;`
  line
  line `(i) "establishment" includes a Government establishment and private establishment;`
  line
  line `(j) "Fund" means the National Fund constituted under section 86;`
  line
  line `(k) "Government establishment" means a corporation established by or under a Central Act or`
  line `State Act or an authority or a body owned or controlled or aided by the Government or a local`
  line `authority or a Government company as defined in section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)`
  line `and includes a Department of the Government;`
  line
  line `(l) "high support" means an intensive support, physical, psychological and otherwise, which may`
  line `be required by a person with benchmark disability for daily activities, to take independent and`
  line `informed decision to access facilities and participating in all areas of life including education,`
  line `employment, family and community life and treatment and therapy;`
  line
  line `(m) "inclusive education" means a system of education wherein students with and without`
  line `disability learn together and the system of teaching and learning is suitably adapted to meet the`
  line `learning needs of different types of students with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(n) "information and communication technology" includes all services and innovations relating to`
  line `information and communication, including telecom services, web based services, electronic and print`
  line `services, digital and virtual services;`
  line
  line `(o) "institution" means an institution for the reception, care, protection, education, training,`
  line `rehabilitation and any other activities for persons with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(p) "local authority" means a Municipality or a Panchayat, as defined in clause (e) and clause (f)`
  line `of article 243P of the Constitution; a Cantonment Board constituted under the Cantonments Act, 2006`
  line `(41 of 2006); and any other authority established under an Act of Parliament or a State Legislature to`
  line `administer the civic affairs;`
  line
  line `(q) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression`
  line `"notify" or "notified" shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(r) "person with benchmark disability" means a person with not less than forty per cent. of a`
  line `specified disability where specified disability has not been defined in measurable terms and includes a`
  line `person with disability where specified disability has been defined in measurable terms, as certified by`
  line `the certifying authority;`
  line
  line `(s) "person with disability" means a person with long term physical, mental, intellectual or`
  line `sensory impairment which, in interaction with barriers, hinders his full and effective participation in`
  line `society equally with others;`
  line
  line `(t) "person with disability having high support needs" means a person with benchmark disability`
  line `certified under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 58 who needs high support;`
  line
  line `(u) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(v) "private establishment" means a company, firm, cooperative or other society, associations,`
  line `trust, agency, institution, organisation, union, factory or such other establishment as the appropriate`
  line `Government may, by notification, specify;`
  line
  line `(w) "public building" means a Government or private building, used or accessed by the public at`
  line `large, including a building used for educational or vocational purposes, workplace, commercial`
  line `activities, public utilities, religious, cultural, leisure or recreational activities, medical or health`
  line `services, law enforcement agencies, reformatories or judicial foras, railway stations or platforms,`
  line `roadways bus stands or terminus, airports or waterways;`
  line
  line `(x) "public facilities and services" includes all forms of delivery of services to the public at large,`
  line `including housing, educational and vocational trainings, employment and career advancement,`
  line `shopping or marketing, religious, cultural, leisure or recreational, medical, health and rehabilitation,`
  line `banking, finance and insurance, communication, postal and information, access to justice, public`
  line `utilities, transportation;`
  line
  line `(y) "reasonable accommodation" means necessary and appropriate modification and adjustments,`
  line `without imposing a disproportionate or undue burden in a particular case, to ensure to persons with`
  line `disabilities the enjoyment or exercise of rights equally with others;`
  line
  line `(z) "registered organisation" means an association of persons with disabilities or a disabled`
  line `person organisation, association of parents of persons with disabilities, association of persons with`
  line `disabilities and family members, or a voluntary or non-governmental or charitable organisation or`
  line `trust, society, or non-profit company working for the welfare of the persons with disabilities, duly`
  line `registered under an Act of Parliament or a State Legislature;`
  line
  line `(za) "rehabilitation" refers to a process aimed at enabling persons with disabilities to attain and`
  line `maintain optimal, physical, sensory, intellectual, psychological environmental or social function`
  line levels;
  line
  line `(zb) "Special Employment Exchange" means any office or place established and maintained by`
  line `the Government for the collection and furnishing of information, either by keeping of registers or`
  line `otherwise, regarding---`
  line
  line `(i) persons who seek to engage employees from amongst the persons with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(ii) persons with benchmark disability who seek employment;`
  line
  line `(iii) vacancies to which persons with benchmark disabilities seeking employment may be`
  line appointed;
  line
  line `(zc) "specified disability" means the disabilities as specified in the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(zd) "transportation systems" includes road transport, rail transport, air transport, water transport,`
  line `para transit systems for the last mile connectivity, road and street infrastructure, etc;`
  line
  line `(ze) "universal design" means the design of products, environments, programmes and services to`
  line `be usable by all people to the greatest extent possible, without the need for adaptation or specialised`
  line `design and shall apply to assistive devices including advanced technologies for particular group of`
  line `persons with disabilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (12064)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Equality and non-discrimination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12064&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall ensure that the persons`
  line `with disabilities enjoy the right to equality, life with dignity and respect for his or her integrity equally`
  line `with others.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government shall take steps to utilise the capacity of persons with disabilities by`
  line `providing appropriate environment.`
  line
  line `(3) No person with disability shall be discriminated on the ground of disability, unless it is shown that`
  line `the impugned act or omission is a proportionate means of achieving a legitimate aim.`
  line
  line `(4) No person shall be deprived of his or her personal liberty only on the ground of disability.`
  line
  line `(5) The appropriate Government shall take necessary steps to ensure reasonable accommodation for`
  line `persons with disabilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (12065)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Women and children with disabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12065&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government and the local`
  line `authorities shall take measures to ensure that the women and children with disabilities enjoy their rights`
  line `equally with others.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government and local authorities shall ensure that all children with disabilities`
  line `shall have right on an equal basis to freely express their views on all matters affecting them and provide`
  line `them appropriate support keeping in view their age and disability.".`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (12066)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Community life.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12066&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The persons with disabilities shall have the right to live in the community.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government shall endeavour that the persons with disabilities are,—`
  line
  line `(a) not obliged to live in any particular living arrangement; and`
  line
  line `(b) given access to a range of in-house, residential and other community support services,`
  line `including personal assistance necessary to support living with due regard to age and gender.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (12067)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Protection from cruelty and inhuman treatment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12067&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall take`
  line `measures to protect persons with disabilities from being subjected to torture, cruel, inhuman or degrading`
  line treatment.
  line
  line `(2) No person with disability shall be a subject of any research without,—`
  line
  line `(i) his or her free and informed consent obtained through accessible modes, means and formats of`
  line `communication; and`
  line
  line `(ii) prior permission of a Committee for Research on Disability constituted in the prescribed`
  line `manner for the purpose by the appropriate Government in which not less than half of the Members`
  line `shall themselves be either persons with disabilities or Members of the registered organisation as`
  line `defined under clause (z) of section 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (12068)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Protection from abuse, violence and exploitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12068&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall take`
  line `measures to protect persons with disabilities from all forms of abuse, violence and exploitation and to`
  line `prevent the same, shall---`
  line
  line `(a) take cognizance of incidents of abuse, violence and exploitation and provide legal remedies`
  line `available against such incidents;`
  line
  line `(b) take steps for avoiding such incidents and prescribe the procedure for its reporting;`
  line
  line `(c) take steps to rescue, protect and rehabilitate victims of such incidents; and`
  line
  line `(d) create awareness and make available information among the public.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person or registered organisation who or which has reason to believe that an act of abuse,`
  line `violence or exploitation has been, or is being, or is likely to be committed against any person with`
  line `disability, may give information about it to the Executive Magistrate within the local limits of whose`
  line `jurisdiction such incidents occur.`
  line
  line `(3) The Executive Magistrate on receipt of such information, shall take immediate steps to stop or`
  line `prevent its occurrence, as the case may be, or pass such order as he deems fit for the protection of such`
  line `person with disability including an order---`
  line
  line `(a) to rescue the victim of such act, authorising the police or any organisation working for`
  line `persons with disabilities to provide for the safe custody or rehabilitation of such person, or both, as`
  line `the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) for providing protective custody to the person with disability, if such person so desires;`
  line
  line `(c) to provide maintenance to such person with disability.`
  line
  line `(4) Any police officer who receives a complaint or otherwise comes to know of abuse, violence or`
  line `exploitation towards any person with disability shall inform the aggrieved person of---`
  line
  line `(a) his or her right to apply for protection under sub-section (2) and the particulars of the`
  line `Executive Magistrate having jurisdiction to provide assistance;`
  line
  line `(b) the particulars of the nearest organisation or institution working for the rehabilitation of`
  line `persons with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(c) the right to free legal aid; and`
  line
  line `(d) the right to file a complaint under the provisions of this Act or any other law dealing with`
  line `such offence:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be construed in any manner as to relieve the police officer`
  line `from his duty to proceed in accordance with law upon receipt of information as to the commission of a`
  line `cognizable offence.`
  line
  line `(5) If the Executive Magistrate finds that the alleged act or behaviour constitutes an offence under the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), or under any other law for the time being in force, he may forward the`
  line `complaint to that effect to the Judicial or Metropolitan Magistrate, as the case may be, having jurisdiction`
  line `in the matter`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (12069)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Protection and safety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12069&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The persons with disabilities shall have equal protection and safety in`
  line `situations of risk, armed conflict, humanitarian emergencies and natural disasters.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Disaster Management Authority and the State Disaster Management Authority shall`
  line `take appropriate measures to ensure inclusion of persons with disabilities in its disaster management`
  line `activities as defined under clause (e) of section 2 of the Disaster Management Act, 2005 (53 of 2005) for`
  line `the safety and protection of persons with disabilities.`
  line
  line `(3) The District Disaster Management Authority constituted under section 25 of the Disaster`
  line `Management Act, 2005 (53 of 2005) shall maintain record of details of persons with disabilities in the`
  line `district and take suitable measures to inform such persons of any situations of risk so as to enhance`
  line `disaster preparedness.`
  line
  line `(4) The authorities engaged in reconstruction activities subsequent to any situation of risk, armed`
  line `conflict or natural disasters shall undertake such activities, in consultation with the concerned State`
  line `Commissioner, in accordance with the accessibility requirements of persons with disabilities`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (12070)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Home and family.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12070&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) No child with disability shall be separated from his or her parents on the`
  line `ground of disability except on an order of competent court, if required, in the best interest of the child.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the parents are unable to take care of a child with disability, the competent court shall place`
  line `such child with his or her near relations, and failing that within the community in a family setting or in`
  line `exceptional cases in shelter home run by the appropriate Government or non-governmental organisation,`
  line `as may be required.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (12071)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Reproductive rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12071&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall ensure that persons with`
  line `disabilities have access to appropriate information regarding reproductive and family planning.`
  line
  line `(2) No person with disability shall be subject to any medical procedure which leads to infertility`
  line `without his or her free and informed consent.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (12072)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Accessibility in voting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12072&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Election Commission of India and the State Election Commissions`
  line `shall ensure that all polling stations are accessible to persons with disabilities and all materials related to`
  line `the electoral process are easily understandable by and accessible to them.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (12073)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Access to justice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12073&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall ensure that persons with disabilities are`
  line `able to exercise the right to access any court, tribunal, authority, commission or any other body having`
  line `judicial or quasi-judicial or investigative powers without discrimination on the basis of disability.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government shall take steps to put in place suitable support measures for persons`
  line `with disabilities specially those living outside family and those disabled requiring high support for`
  line `exercising legal rights.`
  line
  line `(3) The National Legal Services Authority and the State Legal Services Authorities constituted under`
  line `the Legal Services Authorities Act, 1987 (39 of 1987) shall make provisions including reasonable`
  line `accommodation to ensure that persons with disabilities have access to any scheme, programme, facility or`
  line `service offered by them equally with others.`
  line
  line `(4) The appropriate Government shall take steps to—`
  line
  line `(a) ensure that all their public documents are in accessible formats;`
  line
  line `(b) ensure that the filing departments, registry or any other office of records are supplied with`
  line `necessary equipment to enable filing, storing and referring to the documents and evidence in`
  line `accessible formats; and`
  line
  line `(c) make available all necessary facilities and equipment to facilitate recording of testimonies,`
  line `arguments or opinion given by persons with disabilities in their preferred language and means of`
  line communication.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (12074)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Legal capacity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12074&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall ensure that the persons with disabilities`
  line `have right, equally with others, to own or inherit property, movable or immovable, control their financial`
  line `affairs and have access to bank loans, mortgages and other forms of financial credit.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government shall ensure that the persons with disabilities enjoy legal capacity on`
  line `an equal basis with others in all aspects of life and have the right to equal recognition everywhere as any`
  line `other person before the law.`
  line
  line `(3) When a conflict of interest arises between a person providing support and a person with disability`
  line `in a particular financial, property or other economic transaction, then such supporting person shall abstain`
  line `from providing support to the person with disability in that transaction:`
  line
  line `Provided that there shall not be a presumption of conflict of interest just on the basis that the`
  line `supporting person is related to the person with disability by blood, affinity or adoption.`
  line
  line `(4) A person with disability may alter, modify or dismantle any support arrangement and seek the`
  line `support of another:`
  line
  line `Provided that such alteration, modification or dismantling shall be prospective in nature and shall not`
  line `nullify any third party transaction entered into by the person with disability with the aforesaid support`
  line arrangement.
  line
  line `(5) Any person providing support to the person with disability shall not exercise undue influence and`
  line `shall respect his or her autonomy, dignity and privacy.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (12075)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Provision for guardianship.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12075&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, on and from the date of commencement of this Act, where a district court or any`
  line `designated authority, as notified by the State Government, finds that a person with disability, who had`
  line `been provided adequate and appropriate support but is unable to take legally binding decisions, may be`
  line `provided further support of a limited guardian to take legally binding decisions on his behalf in`
  line `consultation with such person, in such manner, as may be prescribed by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the District Court or the designated authority, as the case may be, may grant total`
  line `support to the person with disability requiring such support or where the limited guardianship is to be`
  line `granted repeatedly, in which case, the decision regarding the support to be provided shall be reviewed by`
  line `the Court or the designated authority, as the case may be, to determine the nature and manner of support`
  line `to be provided.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "limited guardianship" means a system of joint`
  line `decision which operates on mutual understanding and trust between the guardian and the person with`
  line `disability, which shall be limited to a specific period and for specific decision and situation and shall`
  line `operate in accordance to the will of the person with disability.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the date of commencement of this Act, every guardian appointed under any`
  line `provision of any other law for the time being in force, for a person with disability shall be deemed to`
  line `function as a limited guardian.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person with disability aggrieved by the decision of the designated authority appointing a legal`
  line `guardian may prefer an appeal to such appellate authority, as may be notified by the State Government for`
  line `the purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (12076)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Designation of authorities to support.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12076&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall designate one or`
  line `more authorities to mobilise the community and create social awareness to support persons with`
  line `disabilities in exercise of their legal capacity.`
  line
  line `(2) The authority designated under sub-section (1) shall take measures for setting up suitable support`
  line `arrangements to exercise legal capacity by persons with disabilities living in institutions and those with`
  line `high support needs and any other measures as may be required.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (12077)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Duty of educational institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12077&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government and the local authorities shall`
  line `endeavour that all educational institutions funded or recognised by them provide inclusive education to`
  line `the children with disabilities and towards that end shall—`
  line
  line `(i) admit them without discrimination and provide education and opportunities for sports and`
  line `recreation activities equally with others;`
  line
  line `(ii) make building, campus and various facilities accessible;`
  line
  line `(iii) provide reasonable accommodation according to the individual's requirements;`
  line
  line `(iv) provide necessary support individualised or otherwise in environments that maximise`
  line `academic and social development consistent with the goal of full inclusion;`
  line
  line `(v) ensure that the education to persons who are blind or deaf or both is imparted in the most`
  line `appropriate languages and modes and means of communication;`
  line
  line `(vi) detect specific learning disabilities in children at the earliest and take suitable pedagogical`
  line `and other measures to overcome them;`
  line
  line `(vii) monitor participation, progress in terms of attainment levels and completion of education in`
  line `respect of every student with disability;`
  line
  line `(viii) provide transportation facilities to the children with disabilities and also the attendant of the`
  line `children with disabilities having high support needs.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (12078)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Specific measures to promote and facilitate inclusive education.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12078&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate`
  line `Government and the local authorities shall take the following measures for the purpose of section 16,`
  line `namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) to conduct survey of school going children in every five years for identifying children with`
  line `disabilities, ascertaining their special needs and the extent to which these are being met:`
  line
  line `Provided that the first survey shall be conducted within a period of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) to establish adequate number of teacher training institutions;`
  line
  line `(c) to train and employ teachers, including teachers with disability who are qualified in sign`
  line `language and Braille and also teachers who are trained in teaching children with intellectual`
  line disability;
  line
  line `(d) to train professionals and staff to support inclusive education at all levels of school education;`
  line
  line `(e) to establish adequate number of resource centres to support educational institutions at all`
  line `levels of school education;`
  line
  line `(f) to promote the use of appropriate augmentative and alternative modes including means and`
  line `formats of communication, Braille and sign language to supplement the use of one's own speech to fulfil the daily communication needs of persons with speech, communication or language disabilities`
  line `and enables them to participate and contribute to their community and society;`
  line
  line `(g) to provide books, other learning materials and appropriate assistive devices to students with`
  line `benchmark disabilities free of cost up to the age of eighteen years;`
  line
  line `(h) to provide scholarships in appropriate cases to students with benchmark disability;`
  line
  line `(i) to make suitable modifications in the curriculum and examination system to meet the needs of`
  line `students with disabilities such as extra time for completion of examination paper, facility of scribe or`
  line `amanuensis, exemption from second and third language courses;`
  line
  line `(j) to promote research to improve learning; and`
  line
  line `(k) any other measures, as may be required.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (12079)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Adult education.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12079&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government and the local authorities shall take measures to`
  line `promote, protect and ensure participation of persons with disabilities in adult education and continuing`
  line `education programmes equally with others.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (12080)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Vocational training and self-employment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12080&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall formulate`
  line `schemes and programmes including provision of loans at concessional rates to facilitate and support`
  line `employment of persons with disabilities especially for their vocational training and self-employment.`
  line
  line `(2) The schemes and programmes referred to in sub-section (1) shall provide for---`
  line
  line `(a) inclusion of person with disability in all mainstream formal and non-formal vocational and`
  line `skill training schemes and programmes;`
  line
  line `(b) to ensure that a person with disability has adequate support and facilities to avail specific`
  line training;
  line
  line `(c) exclusive skill training programmes for persons with disabilities with active links with the`
  line `market, for those with developmental, intellectual, multiple disabilities and autism;`
  line
  line `(d) loans at concessional rates including that of microcredit;`
  line
  line `(e) marketing the products made by persons with disabilities; and`
  line
  line `(f) maintenance of disaggregated data on the progress made in the skill training and selfemployment,`
  line `including persons with disabilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (12081)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Non-discrimination in employment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12081&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) No Government establishment shall discriminate`
  line `against any person with disability in any matter relating to employment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appropriate Government may, having regard to the type of work carried on in any`
  line `establishment, by notification and subject to such conditions, if any, exempt any establishment from the`
  line `provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Government establishment shall provide reasonable accommodation and appropriate barrier`
  line `free and conducive environment to employees with disability.`
  line
  line `(3) No promotion shall be denied to a person merely on the ground of disability.`
  line
  line `(4) No Government establishment shall dispense with or reduce in rank, an employee who acquires a`
  line `disability during his or her service:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if an employee after acquiring disability is not suitable for the post he was holding,`
  line `shall be shifted to some other post with the same pay scale and service benefits:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if it is not possible to adjust the employee against any post, he may be kept on a`
  line `supernumerary post until a suitable post is available or he attains the age of superannuation, whichever is`
  line earlier.
  line
  line `(5) The appropriate Government may frame policies for posting and transfer of employees with`
  line disabilities.
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (12082)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Equal opportunity policy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12082&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every establishment shall notify equal opportunity policy`
  line `detailing measures proposed to be taken by it in pursuance of the provisions of this Chapter in the manner`
  line `as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every establishment shall register a copy of the said policy with the Chief Commissioner or the`
  line `State Commissioner, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (12083)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Maintenance of records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12083&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every establishment shall maintain records of the persons with`
  line `disabilities in relation to the matter of employment, facilities provided and other necessary information in`
  line `compliance with the provisions of this Chapter in such form and manner as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every employment exchange shall maintain records of persons with disabilities seeking`
  line employment.
  line
  line `(3) The records maintained under sub-section (1) shall be open to inspection at all reasonable hours`
  line `by such persons as may be authorised in their behalf by the appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (12084)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Appointment of Grievance Redressal Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12084&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Government establishment shall`
  line `appoint a Grievance Redressal Officer for the purpose of section 19 and shall inform the Chief`
  line `Commissioner or the State Commissioner, as the case may be, about the appointment of such officer.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved with the non-compliance of the provisions of section 20, may file a`
  line `complaint with the Grievance Redressal Officer, who shall investigate it and shall take up the matter with`
  line `the establishment for corrective action.`
  line
  line `(3) The Grievance Redressal Officer shall maintain a register of complaints in the manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government, and every complaint shall be inquired within two weeks of its`
  line registration.
  line
  line `(4) If the aggrieved person is not satisfied with the action taken on his or her complaint, he or she may`
  line `approach the District-Level Committee on disability.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (12085)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Social security.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12085&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall within the limit of its economic capacity`
  line `and development formulate necessary schemes and programmes to safeguard and promote the right of`
  line `persons with disabilities for adequate standard of living to enable them to live independently or in the`
  line `community:`
  line
  line `Provided that the quantum of assistance to the persons with disabilities under such schemes and`
  line `programmes shall be at least twenty-five per cent. higher than the similar schemes applicable to others.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government while devising these schemes and programmes shall give due`
  line `consideration to the diversity of disability, gender, age, and socio-economic status.`
  line
  line `(3) The schemes under sub-section (1) shall provide for,---`
  line
  line `(a) community centres with good living conditions in terms of safety, sanitation, health care and`
  line counselling;
  line
  line `(b) facilities for persons including children with disabilities who have no family or have been`
  line `abandoned, or are without shelter or livelihood;`
  line
  line `(c) support during natural or man-made disasters and in areas of conflict;`
  line
  line `(d) support to women with disability for livelihood and for upbringing of their children;`
  line
  line `(e) access to safe drinking water and appropriate and accessible sanitation facilities especially in`
  line `urban slums and rural areas;`
  line
  line `(f) provisions of aids and appliances, medicine and diagnostic services and corrective surgery free`
  line `of cost to persons with disabilities with such income ceiling as may be notified;`
  line
  line `(g) disability pension to persons with disabilities subject to such income ceiling as may be`
  line notified;
  line
  line `(h) unemployment allowance to persons with disabilities registered with Special Employment`
  line `Exchange for more than two years and who could not be placed in any gainful occupation;`
  line
  line `(i) care-giver allowance to persons with disabilities with high support needs;`
  line
  line `(j) comprehensive insurance scheme for persons with disability, not covered under the Employees`
  line `State Insurance Schemes, or any other statutory or Government-sponsored insurance schemes;`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which the appropriate Government may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (12086)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title Healthcare.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12086&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government and the local authorities shall take necessary`
  line `measures for the persons with disabilities to provide,---`
  line
  line `(a) free healthcare in the vicinity specially in rural area subject to such family income as may be`
  line notified;
  line
  line `(b) barrier-free access in all parts of Government and private hospitals and other healthcare`
  line `institutions and centres;`
  line
  line `(c) priority in attendance and treatment.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government and the local authorities shall take measures and make schemes or`
  line `programmes to promote healthcare and prevent the occurrence of disabilities and for the said purpose`
  line shall
  line
  line `(a) undertake or cause to be undertaken surveys, investigations and research concerning the cause`
  line `of occurrence of disabilities;`
  line
  line `(b) promote various methods for preventing disabilities;`
  line
  line `(c) screen all the children at least once in a year for the purpose of identifying "at-risk" cases;`
  line
  line `(d) provide facilities for training to the staff at the primary health centres;`
  line
  line `(e) sponsor or cause to be sponsored awareness campaigns and disseminate or cause to be`
  line `disseminated information for general hygiene, health and sanitation;`
  line
  line `(f) take measures for pre-natal, perinatal and post-natal care of mother and child;`
  line
  line `(g) educate the public through the pre-schools, schools, primary health centres, village level`
  line `workers and anganwadi workers;`
  line
  line `(h) create awareness amongst the masses through television, radio and other mass media on the`
  line `causes of disabilities and the preventive measures to be adopted;`
  line
  line `(i) healthcare during the time of natural disasters and other situations of risk;`
  line
  line `(j) essential medical facilities for life saving emergency treatment and procedures; and`
  line
  line `(k) sexual and reproductive healthcare especially for women with disability.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (12087)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Insurance schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12087&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government shall, by notification, make insurance`
  line `schemes for their employees with disabilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (12088)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title Rehabilitation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12088&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government and the local authorities shall within their`
  line `economic capacity and development, undertake or cause to be undertaken services and programmes of`
  line `rehabilitation, particularly in the areas of health, education and employment for all persons with`
  line disabilities.
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the appropriate Government and the local authorities may`
  line `grant financial assistance to non-Governmental Organisations.`
  line
  line `(3) The appropriate Government and the local authorities, while formulating rehabilitation policies`
  line `shall consult the non-Governmental Organisations working for the cause of persons with disabilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (12089)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Research and development.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12089&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government shall initiate or cause to be initiated`
  line `research and development through individuals and institutions on issues which shall enhance habilitation`
  line `and rehabilitation and on such other issues which are necessary for the empowerment of persons with`
  line disabilities.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (12090)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Culture and recreation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12090&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government and the local authorities shall take`
  line `measures to promote and protect the rights of all persons with disabilities to have a cultural life and to`
  line `participate in recreational activities equally with others which include,—`
  line
  line `(a) facilities, support and sponsorships to artists and writers with disability to pursue their`
  line `interests and talents;`
  line
  line `(b) establishment of a disability history museum which chronicles and interprets the historical`
  line `experiences of persons with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(c) making art accessible to persons with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(d) promoting recreation centres, and other associational activities;`
  line
  line `(e) facilitating participation in scouting, dancing, art classes, outdoor camps and adventure`
  line activities;
  line
  line `(f) redesigning courses in cultural and arts subjects to enable participation and access for persons`
  line `with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(g) developing technology, assistive devices and equipments to facilitate access and inclusion for`
  line `persons with disabilities in recreational activities; and`
  line
  line `(h) ensuring that persons with hearing impairment can have access to television programmes with`
  line `sign language interpretation or sub-titles.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (12091)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Sporting activities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12091&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall take measures to ensure effective`
  line `participation in sporting activities of the persons with disabilities.`
  line
  line `(2) The sports authorities shall accord due recognition to the right of persons with disabilities to`
  line `participate in sports and shall make due provisions for the inclusion of persons with disabilities in their`
  line `schemes and programmes for the promotion and development of sporting talents.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), the appropriate`
  line `Government and the sports authorities shall take measures to,—`
  line
  line `(a) restructure courses and programmes to ensure access, inclusion and participation of persons`
  line `with disabilities in all sporting activities;`
  line
  line `(b) redesign and support infrastructure facilities of all sporting activities for persons with`
  line disabilities;
  line
  line `(c) develop technology to enhance potential, talent, capacity and ability in sporting activities of`
  line `all persons with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(d) provide multi-sensory essentials and features in all sporting activities to ensure effective`
  line `participation of all persons with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(e) allocate funds for development of state of art sport facilities for training of persons with`
  line disabilities;
  line
  line `(f) promote and organise disability specific sporting events for persons with disabilities and also`
  line `facilitate awards to the winners and other participants of such sporting events.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (12092)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Free education for children with benchmark disabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12092&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Rights of Children to Free and Compulsory Education Act, 2009 (35 of 2009), every`
  line `child with benchmark disability between the age of six to eighteen years shall have the right to free`
  line `education in a neighbourhood school, or in a special school, of his choice.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government and local authorities shall ensure that every child with benchmark`
  line `disability has access to free education in an appropriate environment till he attains the age of eighteen`
  line years.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (12093)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Reservation in higher educational institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12093&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) All Government institutions of higher`
  line `education and other higher education institutions receiving aid from the Government shall reserve not less`
  line `than five per cent. seats for persons with benchmark disabilities.`
  line
  line `(2) The persons with benchmark disabilities shall be given an upper age relaxation of five years for`
  line `admission in institutions of higher education.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (12094)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Identification of posts for reservation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12094&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government shall—`
  line
  line `(i) identify posts in the establishments which can be held by respective category of persons with`
  line `benchmark disabilities in respect of the vacancies reserved in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `section 34;`
  line
  line `(ii) constitute an expert committee with representation of persons with benchmark disabilities for`
  line `identification of such posts; and`
  line
  line `(iii) undertake periodic review of the identified posts at an interval not exceeding three years.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (12095)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title Reservation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12095&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every appropriate Government shall appoint in every Government`
  line `establishment, not less than four per cent. of the total number of vacancies in the cadre strength in each`
  line `group of posts meant to be filled with persons with benchmark disabilities of which, one per cent. each`
  line `shall be reserved for persons with benchmark disabilities under clauses (a), (b) and (c) and one per cent.`
  line `for persons with benchmark disabilities under clauses (d) and (e), namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) blindness and low vision;`
  line
  line `(b) deaf and hard of hearing;`
  line
  line `(c) locomotor disability including cerebral palsy, leprosy cured, dwarfism, acid attack victims and`
  line `muscular dystrophy;`
  line
  line `(d) autism, intellectual disability, specific learning disability and mental illness;`
  line
  line `(e) multiple disabilities from amongst persons under clauses (a) to (d) including deaf-blindness in`
  line `the posts identified for each disabilities:`
  line
  line `Provided that the reservation in promotion shall be in accordance with such instructions as are issued`
  line `by the appropriate Government from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the appropriate Government, in consultation with the Chief Commissioner or the`
  line `State Commissioner, as the case may be, may, having regard to the type of work carried out in any`
  line `Government establishment, by notification and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in`
  line `such notifications exempt any Government establishment from the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Where in any recruitment year any vacancy cannot be filled up due to non-availability of a`
  line `suitable person with benchmark disability or for any other sufficient reasons, such vacancy shall be`
  line `carried forward in the succeeding recruitment year and if in the succeeding recruitment year also suitable`
  line `person with benchmark disability is not available, it may first be filled by interchange among the five`
  line `categories and only when there is no person with disability available for the post in that year, the`
  line `employer shall fill up the vacancy by appointment of a person, other than a person with disability:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the nature of vacancies in an establishment is such that a given category of person`
  line `cannot be employed, the vacancies may be interchanged among the five categories with the prior approval`
  line `of the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The appropriate Government may, by notification, provide for such relaxation of upper age limit`
  line `for employment of persons with benchmark disability, as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (12096)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Incentives to employers in private sector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12096&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government and the local`
  line `authorities shall, within the limit of their economic capacity and development, provide incentives to`
  line `employer in private sector to ensure that at least five per cent. of their work force is composed of persons`
  line `with benchmark disability.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (12097)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Special employment exchange.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12097&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may, by notification, require that`
  line `from such date, the employer in every establishment shall furnish such information or return as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government in relation to vacancies appointed for persons with benchmark`
  line `disability that have occurred or are about to occur in that establishment to such special employment`
  line `exchange as may be notified by the Central Government and the establishment shall thereupon comply`
  line `with such requisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (12098)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Special schemes and development programmes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12098&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government and the local`
  line `authorities shall, by notification, make schemes in favour of persons with benchmark disabilities, to`
  line provide,—
  line
  line `(a) five per cent. reservation in allotment of agricultural land and housing in all relevant schemes`
  line `and development programmes, with appropriate priority to women with benchmark disabilities;`
  line
  line `(b) five per cent. reservation in all poverty alleviation and various developmental schemes with`
  line `priority to women with benchmark disabilities;`
  line
  line `(c) five per cent. reservation in allotment of land on concessional rate, where such land is to be`
  line `used for the purpose of promoting housing, shelter, setting up of occupation, business, enterprise,`
  line `recreation centres and production centres.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (12099)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Special provisions for persons with disabilities with high support.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12099&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person with`
  line `benchmark disability, who considers himself to be in need of high support, or any person or organisation`
  line `on his or her behalf, may apply to an authority, to be notified by the appropriate Government, requesting`
  line `to provide high support.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the authority shall refer it to an Assessment`
  line `Board consisting of such Members as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Assessment Board shall assess the case referred to it under sub-section (1) in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government, and shall send a report to the authority certifying the need`
  line `of high support and its nature.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of a report under sub-section (3), the authority shall take steps to provide support in`
  line `accordance with the report and subject to relevant schemes and orders of the appropriate Government in`
  line `this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (12100)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Awareness campaigns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12100&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government, in consultation with the Chief`
  line `Commissioner or the State Commissioner, as the case may be, shall conduct, encourage, support or`
  line `promote awareness campaigns and sensitisation programmes to ensure that the rights of the persons with`
  line `disabilities provided under this Act are protected.`
  line
  line `(2) The programmes and campaigns specified under sub-section (1) shall also,—`
  line
  line `(a) promote values of inclusion, tolerance, empathy and respect for diversity;`
  line
  line `(b) advance recognition of the skills, merits and abilities of persons with disabilities and of their`
  line `contributions to the workforce, labour market and professional fee;`
  line
  line `(c) foster respect for the decisions made by persons with disabilities on all matters related to`
  line `family life, relationships, bearing and raising children;`
  line
  line `(d) provide orientation and sensitisation at the school, college, University and professional`
  line `training level on the human condition of disability and the rights of persons with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(e) provide orientation and sensitisation on disabling conditions and rights of persons with`
  line `disabilities to employers, administrators and co-workers;`
  line
  line `(f) ensure that the rights of persons with disabilities are included in the curriculum in Universities,`
  line `colleges and schools.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (12101)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title Accessibility.
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12101&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, in consultation with the Chief Commissioner,`
  line `formulate rules for persons with disabilities laying down the standards of accessibility for the physical`
  line `environment, transportation, information and communications, including appropriate technologies and`
  line `systems, and other facilities and services provided to the public in urban and rural areas.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (12102)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Access to transport.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12102&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall take suitable measures to`
  line provide,—
  line
  line `(a) facilities for persons with disabilities at bus stops, railway stations and airports conforming to`
  line `the accessibility standards relating to parking spaces, toilets, ticketing counters and ticketing`
  line machines;
  line
  line `(b) access to all modes of transport that conform the design standards, including retrofitting old`
  line `modes of transport, wherever technically feasible and safe for persons with disabilities, economically`
  line `viable and without entailing major structural changes in design;`
  line
  line `(c) accessible roads to address mobility necessary for persons with disabilities.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government shall develop schemes programmes to promote the personal mobility`
  line `of persons with disabilities at affordable cost to provide for,—`
  line
  line `(a) incentives and concessions;`
  line
  line `(b) retrofitting of vehicles; and`
  line
  line `(c) personal mobility assistance.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (12103)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Access to information and communication technology.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12103&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government shall`
  line `take measures to ensure that,—`
  line
  line `(i) all contents available in audio, print and electronic media are in accessible format;`
  line
  line `(ii) persons with disabilities have access to electronic media by providing audio description, sign`
  line `language interpretation and close captioning;`
  line
  line `(iii) electronic goods and equipment which are meant for every day use are available in universal`
  line design.
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (12104)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Consumer goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12104&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government shall take measures to promote development,`
  line `production and distribution of universally designed consumer products and accessories for general use for`
  line `persons with disabilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (12105)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Mandatory observance of accessibility norms.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12105&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) No establishment shall be granted`
  line `permission to build any structure if the building plan does not adhere to the rules formulated by the`
  line `Central Government under section 40.`
  line
  line `(2) No establishment shall be issued a certificate of completion or allowed to take occupation of a`
  line `building unless it has adhered to the rules formulated by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (12106)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Time limit for making existing infrastructure and premises accessible and action for that purpose.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12106&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) All existing public buildings shall be made accessible in accordance with the rules`
  line `formulated by the Central Government within a period not exceeding five years from the date of`
  line `notification of such rules:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may grant extension of time to the States on a case to case`
  line `basis for adherence to this provision depending on their state of preparedness and other related`
  line parameters.
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government and the local authorities shall formulate and publish an action plan`
  line `based on prioritisation, for providing accessibility in all their buildings and spaces providing essential`
  line `services such as all primary health centres, civil hospitals, schools, railway stations and bus stops.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (12107)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Time limit for accessibility by service providers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12107&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The service providers whether Government`
  line `or private shall provide services in accordance with the rules on accessibility formulated by the Central`
  line `Government under section 40 within a period of two years from the date of notification of such rules:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government in consultation with the Chief Commissioner may grant`
  line `extension of time for providing certain category of services in accordance with the said rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (12108)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Human resource development.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12108&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to any function and power of`
  line `Rehabilitation Council of India constituted under the Rehabilitation Council of India Act, 1992`
  line `(34 of 1992), the appropriate Government shall endeavour to develop human resource for the purposes of`
  line `this Act and to that end shall,---`
  line
  line `(a) mandate training on disability rights in all courses for the training of Panchayati Raj`
  line `Members, legislators, administrators, police officials, judges and lawyers;`
  line
  line `(b) induct disability as a component for all education courses for schools, colleges and University`
  line `teachers, doctors, nurses, para-medical personnel, social welfare officers, rural development officers,`
  line `asha workers, anganwadi workers, engineers, architects, other professionals and community workers;`
  line
  line `(c) initiate capacity building programmes including training in independent living and community`
  line `relationships for families, members of community and other stakeholders and care providers on care`
  line `giving and support;`
  line
  line `(d) ensure independence training for persons with disabilities to build community relationships on`
  line `mutual contribution and respect;`
  line
  line `(e) conduct training programmes for sports teachers with focus on sports, games, adventure`
  line activities;
  line
  line `(f) any other capacity development measures as may be required.`
  line
  line `(2) All Universities shall promote teaching and research in disability studies including establishment`
  line `of study centres for such studies.`
  line
  line `(3) In order to fulfil the obligation stated in sub-section (1), the appropriate Government shall in every`
  line `five years undertake a need based analysis and formulate plans for the recruitment, induction,`
  line `sensitisation, orientation and training of suitable personnel to undertake the various responsibilities under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (12109)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Social audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12109&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government shall undertake social audit of all general schemes`
  line `and programmes involving the persons with disabilities to ensure that the scheme and programmes do not`
  line `have an adverse impact upon the persons with disabilities and need the requirements and concerns of`
  line `persons with disabilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (12110)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12110&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall appoint an authority as it deems fit to be a`
  line `competent authority for the purposes of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (12111)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title Registration.
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12111&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided under this Act, no person shall establish or maintain`
  line `any institution for persons with disabilities except in accordance with a certificate of registration issued in`
  line `this behalf by the competent authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that an institution for care of mentally ill persons, which holds a valid licence under`
  line `section 8 of the Mental Health Act, 1987 (14 of 1987) or any other Act for the time being in force, shall`
  line `not be required to be registered under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (12112)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Application and grant of certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12112&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every application for a certificate of`
  line `registration shall be made to the competent authority in such form and in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the competent authority shall make such`
  line `enquiries as it may deem fit and on being satisfied that the applicant has complied with the requirements`
  line `of this Act and the rules made thereunder, it shall grant a certificate of registration to the applicant within`
  line `a period of ninety days of receipt of application and if not satisfied, the competent authority shall, by`
  line `order, refuse to grant the certificate applied for:`
  line
  line `Provided that before making any order refusing to grant a certificate, the competent authority shall`
  line `give the applicant a reasonable opportunity of being heard and every order of refusal to grant a certificate`
  line `shall be communicated to the applicant in writing.`
  line
  line `(3) No certificate of registration shall be granted under sub-section (2) unless the institution with`
  line `respect to which an application has been made is in a position to provide such facilities and meet such`
  line `standards as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The certificate of registration granted under sub-section (2),—`
  line
  line `(a) shall, unless revoked under section 52 remain in force for such period as may be prescribed by`
  line `the State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) may be renewed from time to time for a like period; and`
  line
  line `(c) shall be in such form and shall be subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(5) An application for renewal of a certificate of registration shall be made not less than sixty days`
  line `before the expiry of the period of validity.`
  line
  line `(6) A copy of the certificate of registration shall be displayed by the institution in a conspicuous`
  line place.
  line
  line `(7) Every application made under sub-section (1) or sub-section (5) shall be disposed of by the`
  line `competent authority within such period as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (12113)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Revocation of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12113&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The competent authority may, if it has reason to believe that the`
  line `holder of a certificate of registration granted under sub-section (2) of section 51 has,—`
  line
  line `(a) made a statement in relation to any application for the issue or renewal of the certificate which`
  line `is incorrect or false in material particulars; or`
  line
  line `(b) committed or has caused to be committed any breach of rules or any conditions subject to`
  line `which the certificate was granted,`
  line
  line `it may, after making such inquiry, as it deems fit, by order, revoke the certificate:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made until an opportunity is given to the holder of the certificate`
  line `to show cause as to why the certificate of registration shall not be revoked.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a certificate of registration in respect of an institution has been revoked under`
  line `sub-section (1), such institution shall cease to function from the date of such revocation:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an appeal lies under section 53 against the order of revocation, such institution`
  line `shall cease to function,—`
  line
  line `(a) where no appeal has been preferred immediately on the expiry of the period prescribed for the`
  line `filing of such appeal; or`
  line
  line `(b) where such appeal has been preferred, but the order of revocation has been upheld, from the`
  line `date of the order of appeal.`
  line
  line `(3) On the revocation of a certificate of registration in respect of an institution, the competent`
  line `authority may direct that any person with disability who is an inmate of such institution on the date of`
  line `such revocation, shall be—`
  line
  line `(a) restored to the custody of his or her parent, spouse or lawful guardian, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(b) transferred to any other institution specified by the competent authority.`
  line
  line `(4) Every institution which holds a certificate of registration which is revoked under this section shall,`
  line `immediately after such revocation, surrender such certificate to the competent authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (12114)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12114&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by the order of the competent authority refusing to grant a`
  line `certificate of registration or revoking a certificate of registration may, within such period as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government, prefer an appeal to such appellate authority, as may be notified by`
  line `the State Government against such refusal or revocation.`
  line
  line `(2) The order of the appellate authority on such appeal shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (12115)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Act not to apply to institutions established or maintained by Central or State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12115&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Chapter shall apply to an institution for persons with`
  line `disabilities established or maintained by the Central Government or a State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (12116)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Assistance to registered institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12116&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may within the limits of`
  line `their economic capacity and development, grant financial assistance to registered institutions to provide`
  line `services and to implement the schemes and programmes in pursuance of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (12117)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Guidelines for assessment of specified disabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12117&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall notify`
  line `guidelines for the purpose of assessing the extent of specified disability in a person.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (12118)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Designation of certifying authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12118&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall designate persons,`
  line `having requisite qualifications and experience, as certifying authorities, who shall be competent to issue`
  line `the certificate of disability.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government shall also notify the jurisdiction within which and the terms and`
  line `conditions subject to which, the certifying authority shall perform its certification functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (12119)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Procedure for certification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12119&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person with specified disability, may apply, in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government, to a certifying authority having jurisdiction, for`
  line `issuing of a certificate of disability.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the certifying authority shall assess the`
  line `disability of the concerned person in accordance with relevant guidelines notified under section 56, and`
  line `shall, after such assessment, as the case may be,—`
  line
  line `(a) issue a certificate of disability to such person, in such form as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) inform him in writing that he has no specified disability.`
  line
  line `(3) The certificate of disability issued under this section shall be valid across the country.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (12120)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Appeal against a decision of certifying authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12120&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved with decision of`
  line `the certifying authority, may appeal against such decision, within such time and in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government, to such appellate authority as the State Government may designate`
  line `for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an appeal, the appellate authority shall decide the appeal in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (12121)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Constitution of Central Advisory Board on Disability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12121&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by`
  line `notification, constitute a body to be known as the Central Advisory Board on Disability to exercise the`
  line `powers conferred on, and to perform the functions assigned to it, under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Advisory Board shall consist of,—`
  line
  line `(a) the Minister in charge of Department of Disability Affairs in the Central Government,`
  line `Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) the Minister of State in charge dealing with Department of Disability Affairs in the Ministry`
  line `in the Central Government, Vice Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) three Members of Parliament, of whom two shall be elected by Lok Sabha and one by the`
  line `Rajya Sabha, Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) the Ministers in charge of Disability Affairs of all States and Administrators or Lieutenant`
  line `Governors of the Union territories, Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) Secretaries to the Government of India in charge of the Ministries or Departments of`
  line `Disability Affairs, Social Justice and Empowerment, School Education and Literacy, and Higher`
  line `Education, Women and Child Development, Expenditure, Personnel and Training, Administrative`
  line `Reforms and Public Grievances, Health and Family Welfare, Rural Development, Panchayati Raj,`
  line `Industrial Policy and Promotion, Urban Development, Housing and Urban Poverty Alleviation,`
  line `Science and Technology, Communications and Information Technology, Legal Affairs, Public`
  line `Enterprises, Youth Affairs and Sports, Road Transport and Highways and Civil Aviation, Members,`
  line `ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) Secretary, National Institute of Transforming India (NITI) Aayog, Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) Chairperson, Rehabilitation Council of India, Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(h) Chairperson, National Trust for the Welfare of Persons with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental`
  line `Retardation and Multiple Disabilities, Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(i) Chairman-cum-Managing Director, National Handicapped Finance Development Corporation,`
  line `Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(j) Chairman-cum-Managing Director, Artificial Limbs Manufacturing Corporation, Member,`
  line `ex officio;`
  line
  line `(k) Chairman, Railway Board, Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(l) Director-General, Employment and Training, Ministry of Labour and Employment, Member,`
  line `ex officio;`
  line
  line `(m) Director, National Council for Educational Research and Training, Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(n) Chairperson, National Council of Teacher Education, Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(o) Chairperson, University Grants Commission, Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(p) Chairperson, Medical Council of India, Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(q) Directors of the following Institutes:`
  line
  line `(i) National Institute for the Visually Handicapped, Dehradun;`
  line
  line `(ii) National Institute for the Mentally Handicapped, Secunderabad;`
  line
  line `(iii) Pandit Deen Dayal Upadhyay Institute for the Physically Handicapped, New Delhi;`
  line
  line `(iv) Ali Yavar Jung National Institute for the Hearing Handicapped, Mumbai;`
  line
  line `(v) National Institute for the Orthopaedically Handicapped, Kolkata;`
  line
  line `(vi) National Institute of Rehabilitation Training and Research, Cuttack;`
  line
  line `(vii) National Institute for Empowerment of Persons with Multiple Disabilities, Chennai;`
  line
  line `(viii) National Institute for Mental Health and Sciences, Bangalore;`
  line
  line `(ix) Indian Sign Language Research and Training Centre, New Delhi, Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(r) Members to be nominated by the Central Government,—`
  line
  line `(i) five Members who are experts in the field of disability and rehabilitation;`
  line
  line `(ii) ten Members, as far as practicable, being persons with disabilities, to represent`
  line `non-Governmental Organisations concerned with disabilities or disabled persons organisations:`
  line
  line `Provided that out of the ten Members nominated, at least, five Members shall be women and`
  line `at least one person each shall be from the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes;`
  line
  line `(iii) up to three representatives of national level chambers of commerce and industry;`
  line
  line `(s) Joint Secretary to the Government of India dealing with the subject of disability policy,`
  line `Member-Secretary, ex officio.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (12122)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Terms and conditions of service of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12122&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided under this Act,`
  line `a Member of the Central Advisory Board nominated under clause (r) of sub-section (2) of section 60 shall`
  line `hold office for a term of three years from the date of his nomination:`
  line
  line `Provided that such a Member shall, notwithstanding the expiration of his term, continue to hold office`
  line `until his successor enters upon his office.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, if it thinks fit, remove any Member nominated under clause (r) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 60, before the expiry of his term of office after giving him a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of showing cause against the same.`
  line
  line `(3) A Member nominated under clause (r) of sub-section (2) of section 60 may at any time resign his`
  line `office by writing under his hand addressed to the Central Government and the seat of the said Member`
  line `shall thereupon becomes vacant.`
  line
  line `(4) A casual vacancy in the Central Advisory Board shall be filled by a fresh nomination and the`
  line `person nominated to fill the vacancy shall hold office only for the remainder of the term for which the`
  line `Member in whose place he was so nominated.`
  line
  line `(5) A Member nominated under sub-clause (i) or sub-clause (iii) of clause (r) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 60 shall be eligible for renomination.`
  line
  line `(6) The Members nominated under sub-clause (i) and sub-clause (ii) of clause (r) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 60 shall receive such allowances as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (12123)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title Disqualifications.
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12123&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall be a Member of the Central Advisory Board, who—`
  line
  line `(a) is, or at any time has been, adjudged insolvent or has suspended payment of his debts or has`
  line `compounded with his creditors, or`
  line
  line `(b) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court, or`
  line
  line `(c) is, or has been, convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government,`
  line `involves moral turpitude, or`
  line
  line `(d) is, or at any time has been, convicted of an offence under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position in the opinion of the Central Government as a Member so as to`
  line `render his continuance in the office is prejudicial interests of the general public.`
  line
  line `(2) No order of removal shall be made by the Central Government under this section unless the`
  line `Member concerned has been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the same.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (5) of section 61, a Member`
  line `who has been removed under this section shall not be eligible for renomination as a Member.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (12124)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Vacation of seats by Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12124&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `If a Member of the Central Advisory Board becomes subject to`
  line `any of the disqualifications specified in section 62, his seat shall become vacant.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (12125)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Meetings of the Central Advisory Board on disability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12125&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `The Central Advisory Board shall`
  line `meet at least once in every six months and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to the`
  line `transaction of business at its meetings as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (12126)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Functions of Central Advisory Board on disability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12126&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `the Central Advisory Board on disability shall be the national-level consultative and advisory body on`
  line `disability matters, and shall facilitate the continuous evolution of a comprehensive policy for the`
  line `empowerment of persons with disabilities and the full enjoyment of rights.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, the Central`
  line `Advisory Board on disability shall perform the following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) advise the Central Government and the State Governments on policies, programmes,`
  line `legislation and projects with respect to disability;`
  line
  line `(b) develop a national policy to address issues concerning persons with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(c) review and coordinate the activities of all Departments of the Government and other`
  line `Governmental and non-Governmental Organisations which are dealing with matters relating to`
  line `persons with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(d) take up the cause of persons with disabilities with the concerned authorities and the`
  line `international organisations with a view to provide for schemes and projects for the persons with`
  line `disabilities in the national plans;`
  line
  line `(e) recommend steps to ensure accessibility, reasonable accommodation, non-discrimination for`
  line `persons with disabilities vis-a-vis information, services and the built environment and their`
  line `participation in social life;`
  line
  line `(f) monitor and evaluate the impact of laws, policies and programmes to achieve full participation`
  line `of persons with disabilities; and`
  line
  line `(g) such other functions as may be assigned from time to time by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (12127)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `State Advisory Board on disability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12127&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government shall, by notification,`
  line `constitute a body to be known as the State Advisory Board on disability to exercise the powers conferred`
  line `on, and to perform the function assigned to it, under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Advisory Board shall consist of—`
  line
  line `(a) the Minister in charge of the Department in the State Government dealing with disability`
  line `matters, Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) the Minister of State or the Deputy Minister in charge of the Department in the State`
  line `Government dealing with disability matters, if any, Vice-Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) secretaries to the State Government in charge of the Departments of Disability Affairs, School`
  line `Education, Literacy and Higher Education, Women and Child Development, Finance, Personnel and`
  line `Training, Health and Family Welfare, Rural Development, Panchayati Raj, Industrial Policy and`
  line `Promotion, Labour and Employment, Urban Development, Housing and Urban Poverty Alleviation,`
  line `Science and Technology, Information Technology, Public Enterprises, Youth Affairs and Sports,`
  line `Road Transport and any other Department, which the State Government considers necessary,`
  line `Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) three Members of the State Legislature of whom two shall be elected by the Legislative`
  line `Assembly and one by the Legislative Council, if any, and where there is no Legislative Council, three`
  line `Members shall be elected by the Legislative Assembly, Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) Members to be nominated by the State Government:—`
  line
  line `(i) five Members who are experts in the field of disability and rehabilitation;`
  line
  line `(ii) five Members to be nominated by the State Government by rotation to represent the`
  line `districts in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no nomination under this sub-clause shall be made except on the`
  line `recommendation of the district administration concerned;`
  line
  line `(iii) ten persons as far as practicable, being persons with disabilities, to represent`
  line `non-Governmental Organisations or associations which are concerned with disabilities:`
  line
  line `Provided that out of the ten persons nominated under this clause, at least, five shall be women`
  line `and at least one person each shall be from the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes;`
  line
  line `(iv) not more than three representatives of the State Chamber of Commerce and Industry;`
  line
  line `(f) officer not below the rank of Joint Secretary in the Department dealing with disability matters`
  line `in the State Government, Member-Secretary, ex officio.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (12128)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Terms and conditions of service of Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12128&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided under this Act,`
  line `a Member of the State Advisory Board nominated under clause (e) of sub-section (2) of section 66, shall`
  line `hold office for a term of three years from the date of his nomination:`
  line
  line `Provided that such a Member shall, notwithstanding the expiration of his term, continue to hold office`
  line `until his successor enters upon his office.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, if it thinks fit, remove any Member nominated under clause (e) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 66, before the expiry of his term of office after giving him a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of showing cause against the same.`
  line
  line `(3) A Member nominated under clause (e) of sub-section (2) of section 66 may at any time resign his`
  line `office by writing under his hand addressed to the State Government and the seat of the said Member shall`
  line `thereupon become vacant.`
  line
  line `(4) A casual vacancy in the State Advisory Board shall be filled by a fresh nomination and the person`
  line `nominated to fill the vacancy shall hold office only for the remainder of the term for which the Member in`
  line `whose place he was so nominated.`
  line
  line `(5) A Member nominated under sub-clause (i) or sub-clause (iii) of clause (e) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 66 shall be eligible for renomination.`
  line
  line `(6) The Members nominated under sub-clause (i) and sub-clause (ii) of clause (e) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 66 shall receive such allowances as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (12129)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title Disqualification.
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12129&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall be a Member of the State Advisory Board, who—`
  line
  line `(a) is, or at any time has been, adjudged insolvent or has suspended payment of his debts or has`
  line `compounded with his creditors, or`
  line
  line `(b) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court, or`
  line
  line `(c) is, or has been, convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the State Government,`
  line `involves moral turpitude, or`
  line
  line `(d) is, or at any time has been, convicted of an offence under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused in the opinion of the State Government his position as a Member as to render`
  line `his continuance in the State Advisory Board detrimental to the interests of the general public.`
  line
  line `(2) No order of removal shall be made by the State Government under this section unless the Member`
  line `concerned has been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the same.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (5) of section 67, a Member`
  line `who has been removed under this section shall not be eligible for renomination as a Member.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (12130)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Vacation of seats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12130&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `If a Member of the State Advisory Board becomes subject to any of the`
  line `disqualifications specified in section 68 his seat shall become vacant.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (12131)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Meetings of State Advisory Board on disability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12131&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `The State Advisory Board shall meet at least`
  line `once in every six months and shall observe such rules or procedure in regard to the transaction of business`
  line `at its meetings as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (12132)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Functions of State Advisory Board on disability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12132&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1)Subject to the provisions of this Act, the State Advisory Board shall be the State-level consultative and advisory body on disability matters, and shall facilitate the continuous evolution of a comprehensive policy for the empowerment of persons with disabilities and the full enjoyment of rights.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, the State`
  line `Advisory Board on disability shall perform the following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) advise the State Government on policies, programmes, legislation and projects with respect to`
  line disability;
  line
  line `(b) develop a State policy to address issues concerning persons with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(c) review and coordinate the activities of all Departments of the State Government and other`
  line `Governmental and non-Governmental Organisations in the State which are dealing with matters`
  line `relating to persons with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(d) take up the cause of persons with disabilities with the concerned authorities and the`
  line `international organisations with a view to provide for schemes and projects for the persons with`
  line `disabilities in the State plans;`
  line
  line `(e) recommend steps to ensure accessibility, reasonable accommodation, non-discrimination for`
  line `persons with disabilities, services and the built environment and their participation in social life on an`
  line `equal basis with others;`
  line
  line `(f) monitor and evaluate the impact of laws, policies and programmes designed to achieve full`
  line `participation of persons with disabilities; and`
  line
  line `(g) such other functions as may be assigned from time to time by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (12133)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `District-level Committee on disability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12133&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall constitute District-level`
  line `Committee on disability to perform such functions as may be prescribed by it.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (12134)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Vacancies not to invalidate proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12134&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the Central Advisory Board`
  line `on disability, a State Advisory Board on disability, or a District-level Committee on disability shall be`
  line `called in question on the ground merely of the existence of any vacancy in or any defect in the`
  line `constitution of such Board or Committee, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (12135)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Appointment of Chief Commissioner and Commissioners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12135&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `by notification, appoint a Chief Commissioner for Persons with Disabilities (hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `"Chief Commissioner") for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification appoint two Commissioners to assist the Chief`
  line `Commissioner, of which one Commissioner shall be a persons with disability.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner`
  line `unless he has special knowledge or practical experience in respect of matters relating to rehabilitation.`
  line
  line `(4) The salary and allowances payable to and other terms and conditions of service (including`
  line `pension, gratuity and other retirement benefits) of the Chief Commissioner and Commissioners shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall determine the nature and categories of officers and other`
  line `employees required to assist the Chief Commissioner in the discharge of his functions and provide the`
  line `Chief Commissioner with such officers and other employees as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(6) The officers and employees provided to the Chief Commissioner shall discharge their functions`
  line `under the general superintendence and control of the Chief Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(7) The salaries and allowances and other conditions of service of officers and employees shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(8) The Chief Commissioner shall be assisted by an advisory committee comprising of not more than`
  line `eleven members drawn from the experts from different disabilities in such manner as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (12136)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Functions of Chief Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12136&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Commissioner shall---`
  line
  line `(a) identify, suo motu or otherwise, the provisions of any law or policy, programme and`
  line `procedures, which are inconsistent with this Act and recommend necessary corrective steps;`
  line
  line `(b) inquire, suo motu or otherwise, deprivation of rights of persons with disabilities and`
  line `safeguards available to them in respect of matters for which the Central Government is the`
  line `appropriate Government and take up the matter with appropriate authorities for corrective action;`
  line
  line `(c) review the safeguards provided by or under this Act or any other law for the time being in`
  line `force for the protection of rights of persons with disabilities and recommend measures for their`
  line `effective implementation;`
  line
  line `(d) review the factors that inhibit the enjoyment of rights of persons with disabilities and`
  line `recommend appropriate remedial measures;`
  line
  line `(e) study treaties and other international instruments on the rights of persons with disabilities and`
  line `make recommendations for their effective implementation;`
  line
  line `(f) undertake and promote research in the field of the rights of persons with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(g) promote awareness of the rights of persons with disabilities and the safeguards available for`
  line `their protection;`
  line
  line `(h) monitor implementation of the provisions of this Act and schemes, programmes meant for`
  line `persons with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(i) monitor utilisation of funds disbursed by the Central Government for the benefit of persons`
  line `with disabilities; and`
  line
  line `(j) perform such other functions as the Central Government may assign.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Commissioner shall consult the Commissioners on any matter while discharging its`
  line `functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (12137)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Action of appropriate authorities on recommendation of Chief Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 2018, s. 3 and the second Schedule (w.e.f. 5-1-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12137&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line Whenever
  line `the Chief Commissioner makes a recommendation to an authority in pursuance of clause (b)`
  line `^1[of subsection (1)] of section 75, that authority shall take necessary action on it, and inform the Chief`
  line `Commissioner of the action taken within three months from the date of receipt of the recommendation:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an authority does not accept a recommendation, it shall convey reasons for nonacceptance to the Chief Commissioner within a period of three months, and shall also inform the`
  line `aggrieved person.`
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (12138)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Powers of Chief Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12138&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Commissioner shall, for the purpose of`
  line `discharging his functions under this Act, have the same powers of a civil court as are vested in a court`
  line `under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) while trying a suit, in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of witnesses;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any documents;`
  line
  line `(c) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(d) receiving evidence on affidavits; and`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents.`
  line
  line `(2) Every proceeding before the Chief Commissioner shall be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Chief Commissioner shall`
  line `be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (12139)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Annual and special reports by Chief Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12139&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Commissioner shall`
  line `submit an annual report to the Central Government and may at any time submit special reports on any`
  line `matter, which, in his opinion, is of such urgency or importance that it shall not be deferred till submission`
  line `of the annual report.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall cause the annual and the special reports of the Chief Commissioner`
  line `to be laid before each House of Parliament, along with a memorandum of action taken or proposed to be`
  line `taken on his recommendations and the reasons for non-acceptance the recommendations, if any.`
  line
  line `(3) The annual and special reports shall be prepared in such form, manner and contain such details as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (12140)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Appointment of State Commissioner in States.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12140&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by`
  line `notification, appoint a State Commissioner for Persons with Disabilities (hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `"State Commissioner") for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as the State Commissioner unless he has special`
  line `knowledge or practical experience in respect of matters relating to rehabilitation.`
  line
  line `(3) The salary and allowances payable to and other terms and conditions of service (including`
  line `pension, gratuity and other retirement benefits) of the State Commissioner shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government shall determine the nature and categories of officers and other employees`
  line `required to assist the State Commissioner in the discharge of his functions and provide the State`
  line `Commissioner with such officers and other employees as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(5) The officers and employees provided to the State Commissioner shall discharge his functions`
  line `under the general superintendence and control of the State Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(6) The salaries and allowances and other conditions of service of officers and employees shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(7) The State Commissioner shall be assisted by an advisory committee comprising of not more than`
  line `five members drawn from the experts in the disability sector in such manner as may be prescribed by the`
  line `State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (12141)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Functions of State Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12141&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `The State Commissioner shall—`
  line
  line `(a) identify, suo motu or otherwise, provision of any law or policy, programme and procedures,`
  line `which are in consistent with this Act, and recommend necessary corrective steps;`
  line
  line `(b) inquire, suo motu or otherwise deprivation of rights of persons with disabilities and safeguards`
  line `available to them in respect of matters for which the State Government is the appropriate Government`
  line `and take up the matter with appropriate authorities for corrective action;`
  line
  line `(c) review the safeguards provided by or under this Act or any other law for the time being in`
  line `force for the protection of rights of persons with disabilities and recommend measures for their`
  line `effective implementation;`
  line
  line `(d) review the factors that inhibit the enjoyment of rights of persons with disabilities and`
  line `recommend appropriate remedial measures;`
  line
  line `(e) undertake and promote research in the field of the rights of persons with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(f) promote awareness of the rights of persons with disabilities and the safeguards available for`
  line `their protection;`
  line
  line `(g) monitor implementation of the provisions of this Act and schemes, programmes meant for`
  line `persons with disabilities;`
  line
  line `(h) monitor utilisation of funds disbursed by the State Government for the benefits of persons`
  line `with disabilities; and`
  line
  line `(i) perform such other functions as the State Government may assign.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (12142)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Action by appropriate authorities on recommendation of State Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12142&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line Whenever
  line `the State Commissioner makes a recommendation to an authority in pursuance of clause (b) of section 80,`
  line `that authority shall take necessary action on it, and inform the State Commissioner of the action taken`
  line `within three months from the date of receipt of the recommendation:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an authority does not accept a recommendation, it shall convey reasons for nonacceptance`
  line `to the State Commissioner for Persons with Disabilities within the period of three months, and`
  line `shall also inform the aggrieved person.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (12143)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Powers of State Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12143&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Commissioner shall, for the purpose of`
  line `discharging their functions under this Act, have the same powers of a civil court as are vested in a court`
  line `under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) while trying a suit, in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of witnesses;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any documents;`
  line
  line `(c) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(d) receiving evidence on affidavits; and`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents.`
  line
  line `(2) Every proceeding before the State Commissioner shall be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the State Commissioners`
  line `shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (12144)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Annual and special reports by State Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12144&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Commissioner shall submit`
  line `an annual report to the State Government and may at any time submit special reports on any matter,`
  line `which, in its opinion, is of such urgency or importance that it shall not be deferred till submission of the`
  line `annual report.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall cause the annual and the special reports of the State Commissioner`
  line `for persons with disabilities to be laid before each House of State Legislature where it consists of two`
  line `Houses or where such Legislature consist of one House, before that House along with a memorandum of`
  line `action taken or proposed to be taken on the recommendation of the State Commissioner and the reasons`
  line `for non-acceptance the recommendations, if any.`
  line
  line `(3) The annual and special reports shall be prepared in such form, manner and contain such details as`
  line `may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (12145)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Special Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12145&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of providing speedy trial, the State Government shall, with the`
  line `concurrence of the Chief Justice of the High Court, by notification, specify for each district, a Court of`
  line `Session to be a Special Court to try the offences under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (12146)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Special Public Prosecutor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12146&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) For every Special Court, the State Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify a Public Prosecutor or appoint an advocate, who has been in practice as an advocate`
  line `for not less than seven years, as a Special Public Prosecutor for the purpose of conducting cases in that`
  line Court.
  line
  line `(2) The Special Public Prosecutor appointed under sub-section (1) shall be entitled to receive such`
  line `fees or remuneration as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (12147)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `National Fund for persons with disabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12147&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Fund to be called`
  line `the National Fund for persons with disabilities and there shall be credited thereto--`
  line
  line `(a) all sums available under the Fund for people with disabilities, constituted vide notification No.`
  line `S.O. 573 (E), dated the 11th August, 1983 and the Trust Fund for Empowerment of Persons with`
  line `Disabilities, constituted vide notification No. 30-03/2004-DDII, dated the 21st November, 2006,`
  line `under the Charitable Endowment Act, 1890 (6 of 1890).`
  line
  line `(b) all sums payable by banks, corporations, financial institutions in pursuance of judgment dated`
  line `the 16th April, 2004 of the Hon'ble Supreme Court in Civil Appeal Nos. 4655 and 5218 of 2000;`
  line
  line `(c) all sums received by way of grant, gifts, donations, benefactions, bequests or transfers;`
  line
  line `(d) all sums received from the Central Government including grants-in-aid;`
  line
  line `(e) all sums from such other sources as may be decided by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund for persons with disabilities shall be utilised and managed in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (12148)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12148&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall maintain proper accounts and other`
  line `relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts of the Fund including the income and`
  line `expenditure accounts in such form as may be prescribed in consultation with the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Fund shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such`
  line `audit shall be payable from the Fund to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any other person appointed by him in`
  line `connection with the audit of the accounts of the Fund shall have the same rights, privileges and authority`
  line `in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of the Government accounts, and in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `production of books of account, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any`
  line `of the offices of the Fund.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Fund as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon, shall be laid before`
  line `each House of Parliament by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (12149)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `State Fund for persons with disabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12149&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Fund to be called the`
  line `State Fund for persons with disabilities by a State Government in such manner as may be prescribed by`
  line `the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Fund for persons with disabilities shall be utilised and managed in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Every State Government shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records of the State`
  line `Fund for persons with disabilities including the income and expenditure accounts in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the State Fund for persons with disabilities shall be audited by the Comptroller`
  line `and Auditor-General of India at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred`
  line `by him in connection with such audit shall be payable from the State Fund to the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(5) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the State Fund for persons with disabilities shall have the same rights,`
  line `privileges and authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `generally has in connection with the audit of the Government accounts, and in particular, shall have right`
  line `to demand production of books of accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to`
  line `inspect any of the offices of the State Fund.`
  line
  line `(6) The accounts of the State Fund for persons with disabilities as certified by the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India or any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit`
  line `report thereon shall be laid before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses or`
  line `where such Legislature consists of one House before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (12150)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Punishment for contravention of provisions of Act or rules or regulations made thereunder.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12150&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `Any person who contravenes any of the provisions of this Act, or of any rule made`
  line `thereunder shall for first contravention be punishable with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees`
  line `and for any subsequent contravention with fine which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but`
  line `which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (12151)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12151&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he had exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section,---`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (12152)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Punishment for fraudulently availing any benefit meant for persons with benchmark disabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12152&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, fraudulently avails or attempts to avail any benefit meant for persons with`
  line `benchmark disabilities, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years`
  line `or with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (12153)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Punishment for offences of atrocities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12153&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line Whoever,—
  line
  line `(a) intentionally insults or intimidates with intent to humiliate a person with disability in any`
  line `place within public view;`
  line
  line `(b) assaults or uses force to any person with disability with intent to dishonour him or outrage the`
  line `modesty of a woman with disability;`
  line
  line `(c) having the actual charge or control over a person with disability voluntarily or knowingly`
  line `denies food or fluids to him or her;`
  line
  line `(d) being in a position to dominate the will of a child or woman with disability and uses that`
  line `position to exploit her sexually;`
  line
  line `(e) voluntarily injures, damages or interferes with the use of any limb or sense or any supporting`
  line `device of a person with disability;`
  line
  line `(f) performs, conducts or directs any medical procedure to be performed on a woman with`
  line `disability which leads to or is likely to lead to termination of pregnancy without her express consent`
  line `except in cases where medical procedure for termination of pregnancy is done in severe cases of`
  line `disability and with the opinion of a registered medical practitioner and also with the consent of the`
  line `guardian of the woman with disability,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may`
  line `extend to five years and with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (12154)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Punishment for failure to furnish information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12154&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, fails to produce any book, account`
  line `or other documents or to furnish any statement, information or particulars which, under this Act or any`
  line `order, or direction made or given thereunder, is duty bound to produce or furnish or to answer any`
  line `question put in pursuance of the provisions of this Act or of any order, or direction made or given`
  line `thereunder, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to twenty-five thousand rupees in respect of`
  line `each offence, and in case of continued failure or refusal, with further fine which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees for each day, of continued failure or refusal after the date of original order imposing`
  line `punishment of fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (12155)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Previous sanction of appropriate Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12155&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `No Court shall take cognizance of an offence`
  line `alleged to have been committed by an employee of the appropriate Government under this Chapter,`
  line `except with the previous sanction of the appropriate Government or a complaint is filed by an officer`
  line `authorised by it in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (12156)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Alternative punishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12156&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `Where an act or omission constitutes an offence punishable under`
  line `this Act and also under any other Central or State Act, then, notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the offender found guilty of such offence shall be liable to`
  line `punishment only under such Act as provides for punishment which is greater in degree.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (12157)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12157&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of, the provisions of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (12158)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12158&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the appropriate Government or any officer of the appropriate Government or any officer or`
  line `employee of the Chief Commissioner or the State Commissioner for anything which is in good faith done`
  line `or intended to be done under this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (12159)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12159&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `or give such directions, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be`
  line `necessary or expedient for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of the period of two`
  line `years from the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be, after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (12160)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Power to amend Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12160&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the recommendations made by the appropriate Government`
  line `or otherwise, if the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by`
  line `notification, amend the Schedule and any such notification being issued, the Schedule shall be deemed to`
  line `have been amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such notification shall, as soon as possible after it is issued, shall be laid before each House`
  line `of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (12161)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12161&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, subject to`
  line `the condition of previous publication, by notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of constituting the Committee for Research on Disability under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of notifying the equal opportunity policy under sub-section (1) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(c) the form and manner of maintaining records by every establishment under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 22;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of maintenance of register of complaints by grievance redressal officer under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of furnishing information and return by establishment to the Special Employment`
  line `Exchange under section 36;`
  line
  line `(f) the composition of the Assessment Board under sub-section (2) and manner of assessment to`
  line `be made by the Assessment Board under sub-section (3) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(g) rules for person with disabilities laying down the standards of accessibility under section 40;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner of application for issuance of certificate of disability under sub-section (1) and`
  line `form of certificate of disability under sub-section (2) of section 58;`
  line
  line `(i) the allowances to be paid to nominated Members of the Central Advisory Board under`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 61;`
  line
  line `(j) the rules of procedure for transaction of business in the meetings of the Central Advisory`
  line `Board under section 64;`
  line
  line `(k) the salaries and allowances and other conditions of services of Chief Commissioner and`
  line `Commissioners under sub-section (4) of section 74;`
  line
  line `(l) the salaries and allowances and conditions of services of officers and staff of the Chief`
  line `Commissioner under sub-section (7) of section 74;`
  line
  line `(m) the composition and manner of appointment of experts in the advisory committee under`
  line `sub-section (8) of section 74;`
  line
  line `(n) the form, manner and content of annual report to be prepared and submitted by the Chief`
  line `Commissioner under sub-section (3) of section 78;`
  line
  line `(o) the procedure, manner of utilisation and management of the Fund under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 86; and`
  line
  line `(p) the form for preparation of accounts of Fund under sub-section (1) of section 87.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (12162)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12162&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, subject to the`
  line `condition of previous publication, by notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act,`
  line `not later than six months from the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of foregoing powers, such rules may provide`
  line `for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of constituting the Committee for Research on Disability under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of providing support of a limited guardian under sub-section (1) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(c) the form and manner of making an application for certificate of registration under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 51;`
  line
  line `(d) the facilities to be provided and standards to be met by institutions for grant of certificate of`
  line `registration under sub-section (3) of section 51;`
  line
  line `(e) the validity of certificate of registration, the form of, and conditions attached to, certificate of`
  line `registration under sub-section (4) of section 51;`
  line
  line `(f) the period of disposal of application for certificate of registration under sub-section (7) of`
  line `section 51;`
  line
  line `(g) the period within which an appeal to be made under sub-section (1) of section 53;`
  line
  line `(h) the time and manner of appealing against the order of certifying authority under`
  line `sub-section (1) and manner of disposal of such appeal under sub-section (2) of section 59;`
  line
  line `(i) the allowances to be paid to nominated Members of the State Advisory Board under`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 67;`
  line
  line `(j) the rules of procedure for transaction of business in the meetings of the State Advisory Board`
  line `under section 70;`
  line
  line `(k) the composition and functions of District Level Committee under section 72;`
  line
  line `(l) salaries, allowances and other conditions of services of the State Commissioner under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 79;`
  line
  line `(m) the salaries, allowances and conditions of services of officers and staff of the State`
  line `Commissioner under sub-section (3) of section 79;`
  line
  line `(n) the composition and manner of appointment of experts in the advisory committee under`
  line `sub-section (7) of section 79;`
  line
  line `(o) the form, manner and content of annual and special reports to be prepared and submitted by`
  line `the State Commissioner under sub-section (3) of section 83;`
  line
  line `(p) the fee or remuneration to be paid to the Special Public Prosecutor under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 85;`
  line
  line `(q) the manner of constitution of State Fund for persons with disabilities under sub-section (1),`
  line `and the manner of utilisation and management of State Fund under sub-section (2) of section 88;`
  line
  line `(r) the form for preparation of accounts of the State Fund for persons with disabilities under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 88.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or where such State`
  line `Legislature consists of one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (12163)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299&sectionId=12163&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_54_00002_201649_1517807328299
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Persons with Disabilities (Equal Opportunity Protection of`
  line `Rights and Full Participation) Act, 1995 (1 of 1996) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the said Act, anything done or any action taken under the said Act,`
  line `shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
